id: pm-sh4x
title: "UX: Telemetry shows 84 'No update flags provided' errors - improve guidance"
description: "Follow-up from telemetry/manual audit: the no-update-flags guidance must not list --message as an update field because --message only annotates history. It should direct users to actual mutation flags or append/comment commands."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: agent-ux,pm-cli,telemetry-insight,ux
created_at: "2026-05-01T22:38:27.522Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-02T11:28:43.106Z"
author: audit-agent
acceptance_criteria: "No-update-flags guidance lists only real update mutation fields, explains --message must be paired with a mutation, and tests cover the guidance."
parent: pm-rrjv
resolution: No-update-flags guidance now distinguishes field-changing update flags from history-only --message context.
expected_result: Agents and users are directed to actual mutation flags or append/comment commands when update receives no fields.
actual_result: Guidance text and regression tests cover --message pairing requirements; focused and full verification passed.
comments[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-01T23:08:21.921Z",audit-agent,"UX improvements from audit: (1) Error guidance for --status closed already redirects to pm close with examples. (2) No update flags error already has clear guidance listing common flags. (3) Enhanced 'Item undefined not found' to detect placeholder IDs (undefined/null/<template>) and suggest checking variable resolution before calling pm. These address the top 3 telemetry error patterns (85+73+56=214 events)."
  "2026-05-02T11:28:21.016Z",codex-agent,"Evidence: telemetry/Sentry audit showed no-update-flags remains a common expected-error path. Updated guidance to explain --message labels history and must accompany a real field mutation; added error-guidance regression coverage. Verified focused guidance tests through pm test, pnpm build, pnpm typecheck, and full 100% coverage."
